- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as the paper deals with detecting sub-events in social media streams. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of improved methods for sub-event detection. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with the task of identifying relevant information within a stream of data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses neural sequence models for sub-event detection.
